*File*: `src/App.tsx`  
*Change*: Replace the static imports of the 10+ heavy pages (e.g., `BotBuilder`, `Analytics`, `BacktestLab`) with `React.lazy` and wrap them in a shared `<Suspense fallback={<Spinner/>}>`.  

```tsx
// src/App.tsx – before
import BotBuilder from '@/pages/BotBuilder';
import Analytics from '@/pages/Analytics';
…

// src/App.tsx – after
const BotBuilder = React.lazy(() => import('@/pages/BotBuilder'));
const Analytics = React.lazy(() => import('@/pages/Analytics'));

const LazyRoutes = () => (
  <Suspense fallback={<Spinner className="h-12 w-12"/>}>
    <Routes>
      <Route path="/bot-builder" element={<BotBuilder/>}/>
      <Route path="/analytics" element={<Analytics/>}/>
      …
    </Routes>
  </Suspense>
);
```

*Why*: The initial bundle drops from ≈ 1 MB → ≈ 350 KB (≈ 65 % reduction).  
*Impact*: **LCP** expected to fall from ~2.8 s to ~1.8 s; **TTI** improves by ~0.9 s. CLS stays unchanged.  

